xstream.spark

Class TimeseriesRDD

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.spark.rdd.RDD<Event>
      • xstream.spark.TimeseriesRDD
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.spark.internal.Logging

    public class TimeseriesRDD
extends org.apache.spark.rdd.RDD<Event>
    TimeSeriesRDD is the primary integration point for Apache Spark and Oracle NoSQL Timeseries. TimeSeries is persisted in Oracle NoSQL as a series of time slots. A time slot logically contains a sequence of Event. The timestamp of consecutive events in a slot are monotonic. A time slot is stored in a single row in Oracle NoSQL database. A TimeSeriesRDD maps integral number of time slots to a Spark partition. The advantage of integrating timeseries with Spark is to use SQL and advanced analysis features of Spark.
    Author:
    pinaki poddar
